  <style>
   Monocrystalline silicon is made from silicon powder
   <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:links" underlined="true">electric blast furnace</style>
   is smelted with a small pile of gallium arsenide powder, and 1 single crystal silicon can be produced in
   <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:links" underlined="true">Plate cutting machine</style>
   cut into 16
   <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:links" underlined="true">silicon wafer</style>
   , requires MV level voltage to handle. When you obtain monocrystalline silicon for the first time, you can obtain the progress "Singlecrystalline Silicon" (Description: Produce a single crystalline silicon).
